Chilean Stocks: CFR Pharmaceuticals, CCU, Colbun and CMPC

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-06T20:00:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/chilean-stocks-cfr-pharmaceuticals-colbun-and-empresas-cmpc.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:06 p.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index rose 0.5 percent to 4,813.64.  CFR Pharmaceuticals SA (CFR CC) gained 20 percent to 115.63
pesos. The Chilean drugs developer has increased 37 percent
since its initial public offering of shares yesterday.  Cia. Cervecerias Unidas SA (CCU CC) increased 2.2 percent
to 5,590 pesos, the largest gain in six weeks.  Chile ’s largest
brewer was upgraded to “buy” from “neutral” at Bank of
America Corp.  Colbun SA (COLBUN)   rose 0.4 percent to 141.8 pesos.
Santiago-based brokerage Celfin Capital reiterated a “buy”
rating for Chile’s third-largest power producer by installed
generation capacity, citing positive perspectives when rains
begin. Colbun posted yesterday a first-quarter loss of $28.9
million, compared with a profit of $22.8 million a year earlier.  Empresas CMPC SA (CMPC)   rose 0.8 percent to 25,199
pesos. The country’s second-largest pulp exporter posted
yesterday first-quarter profit of $141 million, up from $79.5
million a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net . 